                "text": "Copying a prop into state in React -- this is bad practice as all updates to it are ignored. Instead, read props directly in your component and avoid copying props into state."
              },
              "help": {
                "markdown": "Copying a prop into state in React -- this is bad practice as all updates to it are ignored. Instead, read props directly in your component and avoid copying props into state.\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [https://overreacted.io/writing-resilient-components/#principle-1-dont-stop-the-data-flow](https://overreacted.io/writing-resilient-components/#principle-1-dont-stop-the-data-flow)\n",
                "text": "Copying a prop into state in React -- this is bad practice as all updates to it are ignored. Instead, read props directly in your component and avoid copying props into state."
              },
