              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "It's best practice to explicitly pass props to an HTML component rather than use the spread operator. The spread operator risks passing invalid HTML props to an HTML element, which can cause console warnings or worse, give malicious actors a way to inject unexpected attributes."
              },
              "help": {
                "markdown": "It's best practice to explicitly pass props to an HTML component rather than use the spread operator. The spread operator risks passing invalid HTML props to an HTML element, which can cause console warnings or worse, give malicious actors a way to inject unexpected attributes.\n\n<b>References:</b>\n - [Semgrep Rule](https://github.com/yannickcr/eslint-plugin-react/blob/master/docs/rules/jsx-props-no-spreading.md)\n - [https://github.com/yannickcr/eslint-plugin-react/blob/master/docs/rules/jsx-props-no-spreading.md](https://github.com/yannickcr/eslint-plugin-react/blob/master/docs/rules/jsx-props-no-spreading.md)\n",
                "text": "It's best practice to explicitly pass props to an HTML component rather than use the spread operator. The spread operator risks passing invalid HTML props to an HTML element, which can cause console warnings or worse, give malicious actors a way to inject unexpected attributes."
              },
